<subSubSection id="9C9B48BB060EFFFDFF2CFF44018382EE" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D43E1B30060EFFFDFF2CFF44018382EE" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="E6F5C722060EFFFDFF2CFF44036982A3" bold="true" box="[198,321,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Remarks:</emphasis>
Because only two species are known, the division of generic and specific characters is rather arbitrary, but we have attempted to include the usual characters known to be of value for other dolichopodid genera, or those characters anticipated to be constant in 
<taxonomicName id="138160B3060EFFFDFCCCFF31018B82E9" authorityName="Runyon &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="2010" box="[806,931,226,251]" class="Malacostraca" family="Makawidae" genus="Hurleyella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E6F5C722060EFFFDFCCCFF31018B82E9" box="[806,931,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Hurleyella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
